## Observer Pattern

The [observer pattern](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Observer_pattern) is a
software design pattern in which an object, called the subject, maintains a
list of its dependents, called observers, and notifies them automatically of
any state changes, usually by calling one of their methods.

```typescript
interface IObserver<T> {
  update(...data: T[]): void;
}

interface ISubject<T> {
  observers: IObserver<T>[];
  addObserver(observer: IObserver<T>): void;
  removeObserver(observer: IObserver<T>): void;
}
```

The following components currently use the observer pattern:

* [Tab](section-component.html#kssref-component-tab-observer)
* [Tooltip](section-component.html#kssref-component-tooltip-javascript)
